 - treat. Whitsuntide treat. They have them all over here. They have them - they still have 'em in Lancashire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5992378 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12149258\charrsid2455240 This was Whit Monday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11676149 JC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12149258\charrsid2455240 Yes. Always Whit Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5992378 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12149258\charrsid2455240 Did you have processions or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11676149 JC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12149258\charrsid2455240 Yes, I believe - I believe we did - yes, we did. Yes, because I was in the Boys Brigade. And we used to march, with thumping drums
